## 1. Accounting policy

Heritage items recognised by the entity are accounted for in accordance with IPSAS 45 *Property, Plant and Equipment*, paragraphs 67 to 79. A heritage item is recognised as an asset when it meets the recognition criteria in IPSAS 45.13 and its cost or fair value can be measured reliably (IPSAS 45.69).

Heritage items recognised in the statement of financial position are held primarily for their cultural, environmental, historical, natural, scientific, technological, geophysical or artistic significance (IPSAS 45.67).

Some heritage items, where the conditions of IPSAS 45.13 are not met (for example fair value cannot be measured reliably), are not recognised as assets and are instead disclosed only.

## 2. Measurement basis

After initial recognition, heritage items are carried at either cost less accumulated impairment, or at revalued amount in accordance with IPSAS 45.74. Distribution of measurement basis at the end of the reporting period:

